    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to angles, quoins, corners, or corner projections of northern Indian temple structures. In Indian architecture, an angle; plain fillet (moulding); corner wall-division; corner-division of plan and elevation; corner; kōṇa; corner projection. In Indian architecture, a corner (Kaliṅga); karṇa; kaṇika-pāga (Oriyā).</Note_Text>
